Name: Frequency Class
Description: for providing the "Count" of a particular species that fall within a particular frequency class. A frequency class is defined with one or more Frequency Class Descriptors and, in some cases, a Lower and Upper Bound.

Name: Group Summary
Description:
For providing summary information about a particular species that was collected. Also, a Group Summary Count (or Weight) must be
provided.

Name: Individual
Description: For reporting a suite of measurements from a single individual.

Name: Population Census
Description: for providing the "Count“ or "Total Sample Weight" of a particular species found in a sample or collection event.

Name: Species Density
Description: for providing the “Density“ or “Relative Density” of a particular species found in a sample.

Name: Targeted Sampling
Description: For reporting a suite of measurements on a species

Name: Tissue
Description: For reporting lab results on a tissue sample

Name: Toxicity
Description: For reporting the results of toxicity testing on a species.
